comments.text:
Oh man this one has my mind absolutely racing with theories! Firstly. Two young girls with most likely next to no real life experience, full of excitement about this foreign trip in another country.  Then you have a tour guide who seemingly would only take females but no males!  Big red flag.  Then there is a hitman/serial killer allegedly on the loose in the region around the time of their disappearance!  Also itâ€™s rumoured that a cannibal is also thrown into the mix!!  What if not one but two, if not all three of these individuals are responsible for not only the kidnapping of these two young women, but also ultimately their deaths?  
The tour guide sets out with these two young women to go hiking in what I can only imagine to be pretty remote and off the grid routes! Eventually met up with one or even both of these men and abducted them for whatever nefarious means they had it mind?  That in itself doesnâ€™t bear thinking about.
Then there is talk about ritualistic killings!  One of the girls shoes with a foot still inside is found and it seems it cannot be determined as to how it came apart from the leg!  But what if both of these young girls bodies were frozen to the point that the cutting of the limbs would be very clean?  And unless a proper analysis of the skin tissue is conducted then it would be very hard to ascertain as to wether the limbs had been frozen or not!? Then there is the issue of the backpack being found, or I would say was actually placed in a paddy field knowing full well that it would very most likely be found a lot sooner rather than later!  Then the mysterious pictures taken but no real way as to identify who or what is on them!  Depending on the capabilities of the camera used to take the pictures would there be any geo tagging evidence available?  Each picture would have its on time and date stamp and even a set of coordinates as to where these pictures were taken!?  Pic 509 was missing completely so someone would definitely have to have hooked it up to some kind of computer and use an erasing program of some kind to wipe the picture clean from the camera stored memory!  But as I understand it, any remaining pictures would have there own geo tagging information stored in the cameraâ€™s memory and Iâ€™m pretty sure that itâ€™s impossible to erase or tamper with it!  I could be wrong but Iâ€™m pretty sure thatâ€™s how geo tagging works.  Maybe if it is the case they were murdered!  Whoever killed them may have been experimenting on the bodies for the purposes of alleged ritualistic killings?  And.  Did the killer purposely leave the backpack, the shoe with the foot and other pieces of evidence because they are quite simply showing off about what they have done?  And in effect taunting the authorities at the same time?  Who knows? Itâ€™s just a theory so you would have to make up your own mind.  My sincerest condolences to the two young women, their families and anyone affected by this tragedy ðŸ™
